device.name: SF2_MSS_sys
device.description: CMSIS description for SF2_MSS_sys. Created by Microsemi SmartDesign on Wed Jan 24 09:31:54 2018

register.name: PRESCALE
register.description: The system clock cycle is multiplied by the PRESCALE value, resulting in the minimum PERIOD count timebase

register.name: PERIOD
register.description: The PRESCALE value is multiplied by the PERIOD value, yielding the PWM waveform cycle. Example: system clock = 40 ns, PRESCALE register = 255, PERIOD register = 127. The PWM waveforms will repeat every 40 ns / 256 x 128 = 1.31 ms. The resolution of the PWM waveforms will be 1.31ms / 128 = 10.23 micros. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h08

register.name: ENABLE_0_7
register.description: '1' enables each PWM output. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h00

register.name: ENABLE_8_15
register.description: '1' masks each respective bit in the INTERRUPT register. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h00

register.name: PWM1_POSEDGE
register.description: Sets positive edge of each PWM1 output with respect to the PERIOD resolution. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h00

register.name: PWM1_NEGEDGE_DACLEV
register.description: Sets negative edge or DACLevelOut of each PWM1 output with respect to the PERIOD resolution. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h00

register.name: PWM_STRETCH
register.description: When 0, the state of PWMx is determined by PWMx_POS/NEGEDGE register settings. When 1, PWMx is set to PWM_STRETCH_VALUEx. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h0000

register.name: TACHPRESCALE
register.description: Clock prescale setting. Determines effective clock rate for the counter based on PCLK: 0000 = divide by 1 (default) 0001 = divide by 2 0010 = divide by 4 0011 = divide by 8 0100 = divide by 16 0101 = divide by 32 0110 = divide by 64 0111 = divide by 128 1000 = divide by 256 1001 = divide by 512 1010 = divide by 1,024 1011 = divide by 2,048 Others = divide by 2,048. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h00

register.name: TACHSTATUS
register.description: This is a TACH status register which contains one bit per TACH input, indicating whether the respective TACHPULSEDUR register has been updated at least once since the bit was cleared. The bits in this register gets cleared by writing a "1" and "0" doesn't have any effect. This is a R/W1C register with a reset value of 0h0000

register.name: TACHIRQMASK
register.description: This is a TACH interrupt mask register with one bit per tachometer signal, indicating whether CorePWM needs to assert an interrupt if the respective bit in TACHSTATUS register is asserted. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h0000

register.name: TACHMODE
register.description: Sets the measurement mode used for each TACH input. When 0: TACH input is continuously measured and stored in the respective TACHPULSEDUR register When 1: A one-time measurement is performed only if the respective bit in TACHSTATUS register is cleared. This is a R/W register with a reset value of 0h0000

register.name: TACHPULSEDUR_0
register.description: This register stores the number of timer ticks between two successive positive (or negative) edges from the TACHIN[0]. The edge to be used is configurable. If the number of timer ticks exceeds the maximum register value, the value of 0 shall be stored instead. This is a Read only register with a reset value of 0h0000

register.name: CTRL
register.description: Control Register; used to configure the core.

register.name: STAT
register.description: Status Register; read-only value yields the current state of the core.

register.name: DATA
register.description: Data Register; read/write data to/from the serial IF.

register.name: ADDR0
register.description: Slave0 Address Register; contains the default Slave0 programmable address of the core.

register.name: SMB
register.description: Optional SMBus/IPMI Register; configuration register for SMBus timeout reset condition and for the optional SMBus signals SMBALERT_N and SMBSUS_N. Alternatively, enables/disables 3 ms IPMI SCL Low timeout.

register.name: ADDR1
register.description: Optional SLAVE1 Address Register; contains the optional SLAVE1 programmable address of the core. When this SLAVE1 address is fixed, the register will have a R/W bit to enable/disable SLAVE0 comparisons.
